obo:UBERON_0001950  a  owl:Class .

obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1173  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In this study, Ranick et al. used immunogold electron microscopy to investigate the subcellular localization of proline transporter (PROT) in the deep layers of the somatosensory cortex, CPN, and CA1 region of the hippocampal formation. They showed that PROT is enriched in small synaptic vesicles (Fig. 4B). In addition, they used subcellular fractionation of rat brain to show that the proline transporter is enriched in the highly purified synaptic vesicle fraction (Fig. 7).\n\n1/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: For electron microscopy, four adult (250-350 gm) male Sprague Dawley rats (Hilltop Lab) were anesthetized with sodium pentobarbital (150 mg/kg, i.p.) and perfused sequentially through the ascending aorta with (1) 10 ml of heparin solution (1000 U/ml in 0.15 m NaCl), (2) 50 ml of 3.75% acrolein (Polysciences, Niles, IL) and 2% paraformaldehyde in PB, and (3) 200 ml of 2% paraformaldehyde in PB. The brains were removed and post-fixed for 30 min in the latter fixative." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1173" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

